Four Chinese citizens and a China-
based entity had their assets frozen by the Securities and
Exchange Commission on claims of  insider trading .  All Know Holdings Ltd., Sha Chen, Song Li, Lili Wang, and
Zhi Yao faced the action by the SEC over claims they used inside
information to trade in the U.S. shares of Global Education &
Technology Group before the company unveiled plans for a sale to
 Pearson Plc (PSON) , according to an e-mailed statement.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
